{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-mdx-frontmatter-type-mdx-frontmatter-slug-js-content-file-path-content-docs-responsive-examples-aspect-ratio-mdx","path":"/docs/aspect-ratio/","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"id":"f3a555b4-af18-5a68-b908-4896f31bf0c8","body":"\r\nimport { Paragraph } from \"../../../src/components/Mdx/textComponents\"\r\nimport CodeWrapper from \"../../../src/components/Mdx/CodeWrapper\"\r\n\r\n# Aspect Ratio\r\n\r\nThere's only a few aspect ration classes:\r\n\r\n| Class      | CSS rule               |\r\n| :--------- | :--------------------- |\r\n| ratio-auto | aspect-ratio: auto;    |\r\n| ratio-1/1  | aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;   |\r\n| ratio-4/3  | aspect-ratio: 1.33333; |\r\n| ratio-16/9 | aspect-ratio: 1.77778; |\r\n\r\n### Examples:\r\n\r\nHere are a few divs with their aspect ratio set:\r\n\r\n<div className=\"row gap-lg\">\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div className=\"w-full ratio-16/9 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\"></div>\r\n    <Paragraph\r\n      className=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\"\r\n      text=\".ratio-16/9\"\r\n    />\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div className=\"w-full ratio-4/3 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\"></div>\r\n    <Paragraph className=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\" text=\".ratio-4/3\" />\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div className=\"row gap-lg\">\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div className=\"w-full ratio-1/1 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\"></div>\r\n    <Paragraph className=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\" text=\".ratio-1/1\" />\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div className=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div className=\"w-full ratio-auto bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\"></div>\r\n    <Paragraph\r\n      className=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\"\r\n      text=\".ratio-auto\"\r\n    />\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nNone of these divs have an explicit height set. As you can see, `ratio-auto` just does what we'd expect in that situation: a div with a height of zero!\r\n\r\nHere's the HTML\r\n\r\n<CodeWrapper title=\"HTML\" >\r\n\r\n```HTML\r\n<div class=\"row gap-lg \">\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"w-full ratio-16/9 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\" />\r\n    <p class=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\" >.ratio-16/9</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"w-full ratio-4/3 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\" />\r\n    <p class=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\" >.ratio-4/3</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row gap-lg \">\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"w-full ratio-1/1 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\" />\r\n    <p class=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\">.ratio-1/1</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"w-full ratio-auto bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\" />\r\n    <p class=\"text-lg py-md align-center mb-xl\">.ratio-auto</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n</CodeWrapper>\r\n\r\nAspect radios can be made responsive, resize the window below if you're in a browser to watch the ratios change:\r\n\r\n<div className=\"center flex-col my-xl\">\r\n  <div className=\"w-1/2 ratio-16/9 tab:ratio-1/1 scr:ratio-4/3 lg:ratio-16/9 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\"></div>\r\n  <Paragraph\r\n    className=\"align-center text-lg display-none radius-md lg:display-block\"\r\n    text=\"Break Point: lg aspect-ratio 16/9;\"\r\n  />\r\n  <Paragraph\r\n    className=\"align-center text-lg display-none radius-md scr:display-block lg:display-none\"\r\n    text=\"Break Point: scr aspect-ratio 4/3;\"\r\n  />\r\n  <Paragraph\r\n    className=\"align-center text-lg display-none tab:display-block scr:display-none\"\r\n    text=\"Break Point: tab aspect-ratio 1/1;\"\r\n  />\r\n  <Paragraph\r\n    className=\"align-center text-lg display-block tab:display-none\"\r\n    text=\"Break Point: mob aspect-ratio 16/9;\"\r\n  />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nAnd here's the Html:\r\n\r\n<CodeWrapper title=\"HTML\" >\r\n\r\n```HTML\r\n<div className=\"center flex-col my-xl\">\r\n  <div className=\"w-1/2 bg-background-dkr radius-lg border-dotted border-lg\r\n    ratio-16/9\r\n    tab:ratio-1/1\r\n    scr:ratio-4/3\r\n    lg:ratio-16/9 \" />\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n</CodeWrapper>\r\n\r\nThat wraps up the aspect ratio. Happy coding!\r\n","frontmatter":{"description":"Overview of Aspect Ratio","title":"Aspect Ratio","type":"docs","image":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"f3a555b4-af18-5a68-b908-4896f31bf0c8","frontmatter__type":"docs","frontmatter__slug":"aspect-ratio","__params":{"frontmatter__type":"docs","frontmatter__slug":"aspect-ratio"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Aspect Ratio","tags":["responsive","box-sizing"],"type":"docs","description":"Overview of Aspect Ratio","category":"responsive","slug":"aspect-ratio","order":130}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2241216091"],"slicesMap":{}}